<h3 class="section-header">
  Domestic Abuse Act 2021
</h3>

<p>
  Provisions in the Domestic Abuse Act 2021 have the effect of preventing an individual accused of abuse from questioning in person a party or witness in the case who is the victim of the abuse, and also prevents a victim of abuse from questioning in person the accused individual in specified circumstances.
</p>

<p>
  If the court directs that the proceedings be listed for a hearing where oral evidence may be given, form <strong>EX740</strong> (person making the abuse accusation) or form <strong>EX741</strong> (person accused of abuse) 'Application and information needed by the court to consider whether to prevent (prohibit) questioning (cross-examination) in person' may need to be completed so that the court can consider whether questioning in person should be prevented. The court will send the appropriate form with the court order.
</p>
